# Discord Chat Analysis

## 1. Summary
The chat primarily revolves around discussions about various tokens in the ElizaOS ecosystem, including ELI5, JIMMY, DOT, and Eddy. Community members express optimism about these tokens' future performance, particularly in anticipation of the upcoming ElizaOS V2 release. Shaw is mentioned as working on V2, which is apparently nearing completion. There's speculation about potential government interest in ElizaOS, with a mention that the US government had previously added an ElizaOS plugin to the ai.gov GitHub before removing it. The community discusses Auto.fun as a launchpad that will gain attention when projects like Comput3 succeed. A few technical issues are raised, including a dead link on the elizaos.ai website and a question about integrating the web3-plugin. The chat also includes mentions of Shaw potentially integrating ETH support in the future and expectations for significant growth in Q3 for AI agents, especially if ElizaOS V2 succeeds.

## 2. FAQ
Q: What exactly do we get to vote on? (asked by DorianD) A: Unanswered
Q: Is Shaw still in the Eliza project? Don't see Shaw account on X (asked by EddyTheHead) A: He's on Farcaster (answered by DorianD)
Q: When unban official X account? (asked by YEO PO) A: Unanswered
Q: What will happen to ai16z and degenai tokens after the new token is coming? (asked by kevca) A: Unanswered
Q: How can I integrate elizaos/web3-plugin in my backed folder, there is no npm package for it? (asked by Ore) A: Head to #dev-help (answered by Kenk)
Q: How can I ask in some tech channel if I don't have write access there? Do I need some extra invitation? (asked by Robert) A: Unanswered

## 3. Help Interactions

# Discord Chat Analysis: ðŸ’»-tech-support

## 1. Summary
The chat primarily focused on troubleshooting ElizaOS plugin configurations and integration issues. Key discussions included:

- OpenRouter plugin configuration challenges, particularly with embedding support. Users needed to combine OpenRouter with OpenAI for embeddings or use the Venice plugin as an alternative.
- Knowledge upload functionality issues in ElizaOS v1.0.11, with errors during document uploads via both UI and API endpoints.
- Discord plugin configuration problems with token validation.
- Venice AI plugin integration was improved with a new version (1.0.13) that added image support, text-to-speech, and removed OpenAI dependency for embeddings.
- PM2 integration with ElizaOS CLI was resolved using the correct command syntax.
- LiteLLM integration challenges with ElizaOS, with users experiencing 404/429 errors despite correct configuration.
- Docker build issues with package installation failures.
- Twitter plugin configuration requiring specific cookie authentication values.

The most significant development was the Venice plugin update (v1.0.13) which expanded functionality and reduced dependencies.
